  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">*See reports for most recent updates* In response to the ongoing Ebola epidemic, this project will train BRAC&apos;s all-female frontline force of 400 community health promoters to stop the spread of the virus in remote communities in Sierra Leone. These women, trained by BRAC, are known in their own communities and are going door to door, educating people on how to prevent Ebola and recognize symptoms. But they need funding to pay for flyers and leaflets, food and travel costs, and disinfectant.</narrative>
  </description>
